# Auth & Security

## Passwords

- Hash with **argon2id** (`argon2.hash` / `argon2.verify`)
- Use memoryCost `2 ** 16`, timeCost `3`, parallelism `1`
- Never return or log plaintext passwords

## JWT

- Sign with `process.env.JWT_SECRET` and payload `{ id: user._id }`
- Read token from `req.headers.token`
- Protect routes with `CheckToken`; admin-only with `CheckAdmin` (`src/middleware/Admin.middleware.js`)

## Responses

```js
// success
{ message: "...", success: true, user, token }

// failure
{ message: "...", success: false }
```

## Rules

- Do not put role assignment on public signup unless explicitly required
- Prefer verifying users by `_id` from the JWT when the User model uses `email` (lowercase)
- Keep validation min password length at **9** characters (existing Joi)
